#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:1
msgid "Nutritional monitoring and undernutrition"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:4
msgid ""
"Screen for undernutrition and track intake in a nursing home (MR/MRS): "
"risk status, MNA, ESPEN targets and automatic alerts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:8
msgid "How does Resthome identify a resident at risk of undernutrition?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:9
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Resthome applies the AViQ/ESPEN screening rules and updates a status: a "
"weight loss of more than 5% in 1 month or more than 10% in 6 months, a "
"BMI below 23 in a resident over 70, or an MNA overdue by more than 6 "
"months move the resident to Re-screen (MNA). A latest MNA of "
"\"undernourished\" places the resident directly in Undernutrition. The "
"status is recalculated on every weight change and once a day."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:11
msgid "Does the undernutrition category change the dependency allowance?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:12
msgid ""
"No. The dependency allowance depends on the resident's Katz category, not"
" on their nutritional status. Undernutrition monitoring is a clinical "
"tool: it triggers assessments (MNA) and alerts, but has no effect on "
"billing. The Katz category and the allowance are managed elsewhere (see "
"the Katz page)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:14
msgid "Where do the energy, protein and fluid targets come from?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:15
msgid ""
"The ESPEN coefficients (30 kcal/kg, 1 g/kg of protein, 1.6 L for women "
"and 2.0 L for men) are facility-wide settings. Resthome then computes "
"each resident's own target from their weight and sex. The energy band "
"rises to 35 kcal/kg for an underweight resident (BMI less than or equal "
"to 21)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:17
msgid "How is actual intake calculated?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:18
msgid ""
"From the meal services: for each meal served, you record the amount eaten"
" (Amount Eaten: none, 25%, 50%, 75%, fully). Resthome multiplies the per-"
"portion nutritional value of the dishes served by this percentage, adds "
"the logged hydration, then compares the 3-day average with the targets. "
"Dishes must therefore carry their portions and their per-portion values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:20
msgid "Who receives the undernutrition or deficit alerts?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:21
msgid ""
"A daily cron creates a \"to do\" activity. The undernutrition alert goes "
"to the head nurse (then the manager); nutritional deficit or hydration "
"deficit alerts go first to the Kitchen role (dietitian), then to the head"
" nurse, then to the manager. Each alert is capped at once every 30 days "
"per resident to avoid duplicates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:23
msgid "Is nutritional monitoring mandatory to use Resthome?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:24
msgid ""
"No. It is an optional screening feature, designed as a differentiator for"
" MR/MRS. It assists the team but does not replace the judgment of a "
"dietitian or a physician. You can use it as much or as little as you "
"like: it activates as soon as you enter weight, MNA, meals and drinks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:27
msgid ""
"Resthome screens for **undernutrition** and tracks each resident's "
"**intake**, drawing on the geriatric **ESPEN** recommendations and the "
"**AViQ** screening rules. Everything is read in the resident record's "
"**Nutrition tab** and driven from the **Meals dashboard**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:32
msgid ""
"The principle is simple: you enter the **weight**, the **meals served** "
"and the **drinks**; Resthome derives an **undernutrition risk status**, "
"**targets** for energy, protein and fluids, a **coverage** of intake, and"
" raises **alerts** when a resident falls behind."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:37
msgid "A screening tool, not a diagnosis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:40
msgid ""
"Nutritional monitoring helps the team spot frail residents early. It does"
" not replace the assessment of a **dietitian** or a **physician**: the "
"status and alerts are signals to be interpreted, not decisions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:45
msgid "The resident's Nutrition tab"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:47
msgid ""
"Open a resident (the **Residents** or **Meals** app), then the "
"**Nutrition** tab. The tab only appears for residents. It brings together"
" the undernutrition status, the latest MNA, the ESPEN targets, the "
"intake, the diets and the food preferences."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:53
msgid "The undernutrition risk status"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:55
msgid ""
"The **Undernutrition Status** block is **read-only**: Resthome computes "
"it, you do not edit it by hand. It shows a colored badge and the "
"measurements that explain it."
msgstr ""

