msgid "**Energy Target (kcal/day)** — energy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:92
msgid "Weight × 30 kcal/kg (or 35 if BMI less than or equal to 21)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:92
msgid "**Protein Target (g/day)** — protein"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:92
msgid "Weight × 1 g/kg"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:92
msgid "**Fluid Target (ml/day)** — fluids"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:92
msgid "1600 ml (women) / 2000 ml (men)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:128
msgid ""
"The **coefficients** (30/35 kcal, 1 g, 1.6/2.0 L) are set once for the "
"whole facility in [Meal and nutrition settings](../configuration"
"/reglages-repas.md). Resthome then derives each resident's individual "
"target."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:132
msgid "Intake vs needs (3-day average)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:134
msgid ""
"The **Intake vs Needs** block compares what the resident actually "
"consumed with their targets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:137
msgid ""
"The **Today** row shows the day's intake: **kcal**, **protein (g)** and "
"**fluids (ml)**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:139
msgid ""
"Three coverage bars — **Energy Coverage**, **Protein Coverage** and "
"**Fluid Coverage** — give the **3-day average** as a percentage of the "
"target."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:141
msgid ""
"Two indicators, **Nutrition Deficit** and **Hydration Deficit**, become "
"true when coverage falls below the configured threshold (75% by default)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:144
msgid "Two buttons round out the block:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:146
msgid "**Log Drink** quickly records a drink for this resident."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:147
msgid "**Hydration History** opens their drinks log."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:149
msgid "For coverage to fill in"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:152
msgid ""
"Food intake comes from the **meal services**: at each meal, record the "
"**amount eaten** (see below). The **dishes** must carry their "
"**portions** and their **per-portion** values (kcal, protein), otherwise "
"the intake stays at zero. Hydration comes from the **logged drinks**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:158
msgid "Logging food intake"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:160
msgid ""
"Energy and protein intake is derived from the **meal services**. On a "
"service, the **Amount Eaten** field offers: **Not Eaten**, **25%**, "
"**50%**, **75%** and **Fully Eaten**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:164
msgid ""
"Resthome multiplies the **per-portion** nutritional value of the dishes "
"served by this percentage to obtain the meal's actual intake, then takes "
"the **3-day average**. Meal-by-meal entry is done in **Meals → "
"Operations** (Meal services, Distribution) — see [Menus, diets and "
"hydration](menus-regimes.md)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:169
msgid "Recording hydration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:171
msgid ""
"Drinks are logged throughout the day in **Meals → Operations → "
"Hydration**, a directly editable list (quick entry). Each line records "
"the resident, the time, the **quantity in milliliters** and the **drink "
"type**: water, coffee/tea, juice/soda, milk/dairy, soup/broth, oral "
"supplement, other."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:176
msgid ""
"You can also log a drink in one click from the Nutrition tab, with the "
"**Log Drink** button. Resthome adds up the day's drinks, computes the "
"**fluid coverage** over 3 days and raises an alert if intake is "
"insufficient."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:182
msgid "The nutrition dashboard"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:184
msgid ""
"Open **Meals → Statistics**: below the general cards (Residents, Menus, "
"Alerts), the page brings together three nutritional banners that only "
"appear if they concern at least one resident."
msgstr ""

