msgid ""
"In addition to the activities, the Nutrition tab shows a **warning "
"banner** at the top as soon as the status is Re-screen (MNA) or "
"Undernutrition, recalling the weight loss and prompting to redo the MNA."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:215
msgid "Set the deficit threshold"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:218
msgid ""
"The **75%** coverage threshold that triggers the deficit alerts is "
"changed in [Meal and nutrition settings](../configuration/reglages-"
"repas.md). Lower it to be alerted later, raise it to be alerted earlier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:223
msgid "Key takeaways"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:225
msgid ""
"The resident's **Nutrition tab** brings together the undernutrition "
"status, latest MNA, ESPEN targets and intake coverage — read-only for the"
" computed measurements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:227
msgid ""
"The **undernutrition status** follows the AViQ/ESPEN rules: weight loss, "
"age-adjusted BMI, overdue MNA or \"undernourished\" MNA."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:229
msgid ""
"The **targets** (energy, protein, fluids) are specific to each resident, "
"computed from their weight and sex using the configurable ESPEN "
"coefficients."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:231
msgid ""
"The **intake** is derived from the **amount eaten** at meals and the "
"**logged drinks**; coverage is a 3-day average."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/repas/suivi-nutritionnel.md:233
msgid ""
"The **Meals dashboard** (Statistics) and the **daily alerts** surface at-"
"risk residents; this monitoring does **not** change the allowance, which "
"depends on the Katz category."
msgstr ""

